  "prompt": "Is spray paint waterproof?",
  "response": "Spray paint itself is not inherently waterproof, but many spray paints are water-resistant once they dry. The degree of water resistance can depend on the type of spray paint and the surfaces it is applied to. Some spray paints are specifically formulated to be weather-resistant or suitable for outdoor use, which often implies a higher level of resistance to water and moisture.\n\nIf you need a waterproof finish, you might want to look for spray paints labeled as suitable for outdoor or marine use. Additionally, applying a clear sealant or topcoat over the spray paint can enhance its water resistance, making the surface more durable against moisture.",
